=>\n      implicit val implicitMaterializer: Materializer = materializer\n      val bytes: Array[Byte] = \"stream-converter-input\".getBytes(\"UTF-8\")\n\n      val result: ByteString = await(\n        StreamConverters\n          .fromInputStream(() => new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes), chunkSize = 5)\n          .runFold(ByteString.empty)(_ ++ _)\n      )\n\n      assertEquals(ByteString(bytes), result)\n  }\n\n  private def withStreamSystem(name: String)(testBody: (ActorSystem, Materializer) => Unit): Unit = {\n    val system: ActorSystem = ActorSystem(name)\n    val materializer: Materializer = SystemMaterializer(system).materializer\n    try testBody(system, materializer)\n    finally Await.result(system.terminate(), awaitTimeout)\n  }\n\n  private def await[T](future: Future[T]): T = Await.result(future, awaitTimeout)\n}\n"}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering asynchronous failures**\n\nI'm thinking about how failures terminate the stream. If that happens, does it mean that future events for 4/5 weren't processed? It looks like mapAsync emits 1 and 4, then a failure occurs, leading to a recovery that emits -1 and completes. I expected to see Seq(1, 4, -1). Maybe I need to use ExecutionContext. But I wonder if maintaining order is possible during asynchronous failures. It's a bit tricky!\n\n**Considering test adjustments**\n\nI'm looking at the dependencies: I want to ensure none are needed. Maybe the Akka CoordinatedShutdown is defaulting to run, but that seems okay for termination. I definitely need all tests to complete in under 60 seconds, without any sleep. Also, it seems the top-level class in my Scala test, `class Akka_stream_2_13Test`, should be public. I wonder if I should stick to that class name style? Modifying only the test file is an option.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07ee84fe5b83e1d20169fabfb63884819396716e7b73068fc9\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-r_mSXrXYtmGH-tjt3xfhuZTvByLtP1Lwq00yXqgNn3NCHRotaGBNWh-GgBqOYCKN-1rX5gT8iurlI0-PethtBF7-ahUcQBLDXhzgnXUuzh4ALTuqzUp0Z1BijxDK2KpEGkHGNGA_gf8PfQa65kjRpO-J1Dft4aE4sUP8IDE8Ue3-YbQeRQJljvZ3_BBfNk12DcMEdblMwDv8w2h0oDPEOWWjyaZQwpD81y5j1CeGvoY2x0He424l88Wgytzg3dgkwhbAMyZR8yK9qT71w-m_VlO8PRVrN_ELyh4h4CGfAWoJEVAtMXP4IfQCDGKIAdWuLq_Qhl6XEdsV4RLcQOmnNAUx_ZYmFI1amUUjCs8V1E1Vkh_boqQ0LVcNxYpxK7lWblAqtSG_NDGoOogrWcpFyw9c-2LRqqBbx_bmpABXVg5vVvH0RprrhJShxt_bsupwnW2Tn3gwZqm9B0ojEjLS1mR-385DC7wO35XT_Gmz1YCIbIfkVi9Dw-0YJ3vJ3pRci3Afmz3Lpm5wRTVvh1utz2O-jqw6jFA0_WSLTo-CFSVS1-SfJNOtt6GAaK4321m41-3_C6qfTp6QBQtSID5ZgeGvTkaEPdohcEL2fieIBYV2vlOHjstug9AjaUuTJic5tt7DGPP3sP4Uz5hAOQ86wteL6gxd1o24S5ylhfegg_CQHRA-RnQKJXPVo9CGiFfzBp8pC6BQoo_edFLkNK6FcplD185rdQXHRrCgv6nK0aadcZOeQT7TEBQuipS_djMQNpSpZuV9od_VviZySr0oPcgbvT2JOE6bzI-r8oReJy-qf2yRth